      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;research-interest&#34;&gt;Research Interest&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My research is focused on &lt;strong&gt;directional statistics&lt;/strong&gt;, a field of statistics where data supports are different than the Euclidean. Specifically, I am interested in hypothesis testing problems with data lying on the hypersphere&#xA;&#xA;    $$&#xA;    \mathbb{S}^q:=\{\mathbf{x}\in \mathbb{R}^{q&amp;#43;1}:\|\mathbf{x}\|= 1\}, q\geq 1.$$&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;My PhD research, advised by &lt;a href=&#34;https://egarpor.github.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Eduardo García-Portugués&lt;/a&gt;, aims to develop one- and $k$-samples tests of uniformity on the hypersphere.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Other of my interests include $p$-value combination methods and asymptotic theory.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
